&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and grow the team:&lt;/strong&gt; Hire, mentor, and manage a high-performing electrical engineering team, providing technical direction, design reviews, and coaching to support strong execution and long-term team development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own system architecture:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and drive the electrical architecture for both Antora’s thermal battery modules and plant-level electrical systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive hardware development:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead development of high-power, high-current electrical heating and power systems from early concept through detailed design, validation, site deployment, and operational support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advance R&amp;amp;D and innovation:&lt;/strong&gt; Evaluate power delivery approaches, including AC and DC system architectures, to optimize for performance, efficiency, reliability, manufacturability, and cost.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner cross-functionally:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with mechanical, reliability, software, procurement, manufacturing, and project execution teams to ensure cohesive system development and successful program delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensure compliance and quality:&lt;/strong&gt; Oversee electrical code compliance and standards alignment, including UL and NEC requirements, while maintaining a high bar for safety, reliability, and regulatory readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build engineering systems:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish and reinforce strong eng

