&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Antora is&amp;nbsp;seeking a self-driven and passionate &lt;strong&gt;Senior or Staff Mechanical Engineer, Fluid Systems&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Product Development Team. In this role, you will own the design, analysis, and validation of subsystems that make Antora’s thermal battery possible. Your work will directly accelerate the demonstration and deployment of a first-of-a-kind long-duration energy storage technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a highly collaborative, hands-on role where you’ll work across disciplines to scope, design, and refine mechanical systems from concept through prototyping, testing, and production. You’ll also help build the processes, standards, and culture that enable our team to deliver at scale&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be excited to pair strong first-principles engineering with modern tools, including AI-enabled workflows where they meaningfully improve speed, insight, or iteration quality. Just as important, you’ll bring the judgment to validate outputs, challenge assumptions, and keep engineering rigor at the center of every decision.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
