&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Antora builds and deploys thermal energy storage to power always-on industrial operations and data centers with low-cost energy. Factory-built in California, Antora’s thermal batteries deliver reliable and cost-effective heat and power for industrial loads of any size. Antora is electrifying global industry while supporting U.S. manufacturing jobs, lowering costs for energy consumers, and enhancing the competitiveness of American industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are growing our company with people who put team and mission first, value connection through laughter and joy, and build with humility and openness. We are committed to continue building a diverse, passionate, and creative team dedicated to a future where every industrial facility, everywhere on earth, is powered by abundant, clean, low-cost energy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Antora Energy is building thermal energy storage plants that deliver zero-carbon industrial heat and power at scale. We are looking for a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Senior / Staff Turbomachinery Systems Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the definition, integration, and execution of the power island across our heat-to-power and combined heat and power projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;As a key member of Antora’s engineering team, &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;you will own steam turbine system&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;architecture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; for heat-to-power and CHP applications, making cross-functional trade-off decisions across thermal, mechanical, process, electrical, and controls systems. Your work will directly influence plant cost, performance, reliability, operability, and execution risk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;You will work closely with EPC partners, turbine OEMs, and internal engineering teams to translate project requirements into executable designs that meet Antora’s technical and commercial objectives. This role will shape projects from early concept development through execution, commissioning, operations, and future fleet optimization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also looking for someone who is excited to improve how engineering work gets done. You will help identify and apply AI-enabled tools and workflows to accelerate analysis, streamline technical evaluations, and increase team leverage across design, execution, and operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Definition&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead steam turbine system definition, sizing, and trade studies for steam turbine islands and adjacent cycles, including sCO₂ and Brayton cycles where applicable. Balance thermal performance, capital cost, operability, execution schedule, and long-term reliability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Influence plant-level decisions related to cycle conditions, heat rejection architecture, extraction and regeneration strategy, startup and transient behavior, and cycling versus baseload operation in thermal energy storage applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Integration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Drive cross-discipline integration across thermal, mechanical, process, electrical, and controls scope, from heat source interface through generator terminals and balance-of-plant tie-ins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Third-Party Interfaces&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Serve as the technical lead for turbine OEM and EPC engagement, including RFP development, bid evaluation, technical clarifications, design reviews, and contract

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Antora builds and deploys thermal energy storage to power always-on industrial operations and data centers with low-cost energy. Factory-built in California, Antora’s thermal batteries deliver reliable and cost-effective heat and power for industrial loads of any size. Antora is electrifying global industry while supporting U.S. manufacturing jobs, lowering costs for energy consumers, and enhancing the competitiveness of American industry.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are growing our company with people who put team and mission first, value connection through laughter and joy, and build with humility and openness. We are committed to continue building a diverse, passionate, and creative team dedicated to a future where every industrial facility, everywhere on earth, is powered by abundant, clean, low-cost energy.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Antora is seeking a skilled and motivated Sr. Electrical Engineer to join our growing team. As an Electrical Engineer, you will play a crucial role in developing electrical systems for our innovative thermal energy storage system. Your expertise will be essential in defining electrical scope and ensuring compliance with applicable codes, standards, and safety practices. This role requires a deep understanding of electrical distribution, transformation, and control of large (&amp;gt;100MW) medium voltage systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roles &amp;amp; Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, configure, and specify medium-voltage protective relay architectures and control schematics. Author protective relay settings files, logic matrices, and point-to-point wiring diagrams for utility-grade microprocessor-based relays (e.g., SEL, GE).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute advanced electrical power system studies, including load flow, short-circuit calculation, motor starting, transient stability, and arc-flash hazard analysis in absolute accordance with IEEE and NFPA guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support electrical engineering, construction, and commissioning activities at the Company’s R&amp;amp;D sites, including installation of transformers, panelboards, cables and raceways, grounding system, and protective devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review vendor materials quotations, evaluate technical bid evaluations, and recommend selections based on technical merit along with price and delivery. Collaborate with Supply Chain to procure equipment and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate engineering/design execution, planning, and interface to ensure compliance with applicable codes, environmental guidelines, quality assurance program, project schedule, and budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of equipment and cable sizing, grounding calculations, lighting, conduit/cable tray fill, and electrical studies (load flow, short circuit, protection coordination, and transient stability)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define electrical architecture and develop one-line diagrams for the first-of-its-kind thermal storage R&amp;amp;D and commercial facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare electrical load lists and equipment datasheets, develop specifications, commissioning, and maintenance procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BSEE with at least 5 years of related experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electrical equipment requisitioning experience up to 35kV.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electrical Power System studies experience with ETAP or SKM Power Tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with protective relays and electrical control

