&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After training, independently perform TPV cell characterization using photoluminescence (PL), external quantum efficiency (EQE), Fourier transform infrared reflectance (FTIR), current-voltage (IV), and other cell and test-article measurements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;After training, independently perform TPV module characterization using PL, electroluminescence (EL), lock-in thermography (LIT), IV, and Thermal Tester measurements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute measurement system monitoring, update run charts, and flag if measurement systems fall out of control.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute reliability tests — stress testing, thermal cycling, and long-duration performance monitoring — and support failure analysis efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn the basics of how the measurement systems and software operate and the meaning and implications for the data they collect on TPV development and manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform data cleaning, exploration, and visualization; identify and report inconsistencies, oddities, or non-physical results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate technical and non-technical content clearly and maintain reproducible documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support routine calibrations and system maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn basic troubleshooting approaches and know when to ask for help.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
